ions in a way that changes how interactions scale at low\nenergies, in particular allowing $1-c_s$ to be larger than derivative-measuring\nquantities like $(H/M_p)^2$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Oct 2019 16:13:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
