 increases\nby $85-430$ Myr and $200-390$ Myr for massive WDs. Although abundant, we do not\nfind evidence that WDs from mergers significantly alter the shape of the WD\nmass distribution. Conclusions: Assuming SSE for inferring properties of single\nWDs gives rise to intrinsic errors as single WDs can also be formed following a\nbinary merger. Strategies for mitigating the effect of mergers on the WD age\ndistributions are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Oct 2019 17:57:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Apr 2020 22:05:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-23"}
