ly analog to the first generation of galaxies. Our\nmeasurements yield insight into the role that X-ray emission from stellar\npopulations in the first generation of galaxies may play in re-ionizing the\nUniverse. This observation paves the way for future strong lensing-assisted\nX-ray studies of distant galaxies reaching orders of magnitude below the\ndetection limits of current deep fields, and previews the depths that will be\nattainable with future X-ray observatories.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Oct 2019 18:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-15"}
