times. The mass entrainment induces thermal energy losses from the background\nand kinetic energy losses from the stream, which we model analytically. Roughly\nhalf of the dissipated energy is radiated away from gas with $T<5\\times\n10^4{\\rm K}$, suggesting much of it will be emitted in Ly$\\alpha$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Oct 2019 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Mar 2020 23:09:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-08"}
